The Mushi Mushi *core* server (everything under `packages/server`,
`packages/agents`, and `packages/verify` that is NOT inside an `ee/` directory)
is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPLv3) — use it,
self-host it, fork it, and modify it for your own org. If you offer a *modified*
server as a network service, publish your changes under AGPLv3 (§13) or obtain a
commercial license (see /COMMERCIAL-LICENSE.md). The MIT SDK packages remain MIT.

The code in THIS `ee/` directory is the **Enterprise Edition**. It is
source-available so you can read, audit, modify, and test it, but **production
use of EE features requires a valid commercial license key**
(`MUSHI_EE_LICENSE_KEY`) issued by the licensor, or an active Mushi Mushi
Enterprise subscription. Without a key, EE features are for development,
evaluation, and contribution only.

This is the open-core model used by projects like Grafana, GitLab, and
Sentry: a genuinely open AGPL core, plus a small commercial boundary that
funds the project.

